Operatives of the Eagle-Net Patrol team on stop and search duty have arrested two suspected armed robbers along the Sapele-Warri Expressway in Delta State. The suspects include Joshua Stephen, aged 20 and Wisdom Obanor, 21 years. The Police also recovered from the suspects, one locally-made pistol and two live cartridges. The Police intercepted an Audi Saloon car with Reg. No: QA 480 UGH, carrying two suspicious-looking occupants. The Delta State Police Command Le by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. He said, “The team subjected them to a search during which, one locally-made pistol and two live cartridges were recovered from them.”